var documenterSearchIndex = {"docs":
[{"location":"roadmap/","page":"-","title":"-","text":"partial_solve!: Partially solve the puzzle\nfor all the positions, check whether the position is stable i.e. satisfiability with the added negation of the position assertion. Some of the positions will end up valid and some would be non-stable and allow multiple solutions.\nIssue with the possible permutations that are not stable but some attributes still belong together.\nInteractiveSolver: Optimizations that are \nStore the InteractiveSolver in the puzzle and avoid constructing the satisfiability problem from the beginning each time.\nIncompletePuzzle <: PuzzleError <-> check_complete:  Check whether the puzzle clues contain all the attributes\nabstract type Question end: Stating the question of the puzzle \ncould be the PositionQuestion, AttributionQuestion, CompleteQuestion\nbased on these, it would be determined whether the puzzle is solvable instead of requiring the complete solution (CompleteQuestion solution) by default\n@clue_str: A better stating of clues\nAn example would be clue\"Hat[Sombrero] -> Pos[1]\", clue\"Hat[Sombrero] <=> House[red]\", clue\"House[red] + 1 -> House[blue]\" etc.","category":"page"},{"location":"reference/#API-Reference","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"reference/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"This page provides a reference for the modules, functions, and types in ZebraPuzzles.jl.","category":"page"},{"location":"reference/#Modules","page":"API Reference","title":"Modules","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"reference/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"ZebraPuzzles: The main module of the package.","category":"page"},{"location":"reference/#Functions","page":"API Reference","title":"Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"reference/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"add_clues!: Add clues to a puzzle.\nadd_clue!: Add a single clue to a puzzle.\nattributes: Get the attributes of a puzzle.\nriddle: Get the clues of a puzzle.\nnclue: Get the number of clues in a puzzle.\nnattr: Get the number of attributes in a puzzle.\nsolve!: Solve a zebra puzzle.","category":"page"},{"location":"reference/#Types","page":"API Reference","title":"Types","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"reference/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"ZebraPuzzle: Abstract type for any zebra puzzle.\nSolvedZebraPuzzle: A solved zebra puzzle.\nUnsolvedZebraPuzzle: An unsolved zebra puzzle.\nAttribute: Abstract type for all attributes.\nClue: Abstract type for all clues.\nDirectClue: A direct association between two attributes.\nPositionClue: A clue that specifies the position of an attribute.","category":"page"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.ZebraPuzzles","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.ZebraPuzzles","text":"ZebraPuzzles\n\nDefines logic puzzles of the zebra kind. This module has the logic to define, generate and solve these puzzles as well as phrase them in plain text and markdown.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"module"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA","text":"EINSTEINS_ZEBRA isa SolvedZebraPuzzle\n\nThis is the famous zebra puzzle that gave zebra puzzles their name. It is said to be created by Albert Einstein. You can learn more about it at the Wikipedia Zebra Puzzle entry.\n\njulia> ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA\nSolvedZebraPuzzle{5, 5, Tuple{House, Nationality, Drink, Smoke, Pet}} with 14 clues\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ House   Nationality      Smoke         Drink       Pet   │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ yellow   Norwegian       Kools         water       fox   │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  blue    Ukrainian   Chesterfields      tea       horse  │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  red    Englishman     Old Gold         milk      snails │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ ivory    Spaniard    Lucky Strike   orange juice   dog   │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ green    Japanese     Parliaments      coffee     zebra  │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\nclues:\n1) Nationality(\"Englishman\") ⟹ House(\"red\")\n2) Nationality(\"Spaniard\") ⟹ Pet(\"dog\")\n3) Drink(\"coffee\") ⟹ House(\"green\")\n4) Nationality(\"Ukrainian\") ⟹ Drink(\"tea\")\n5) Pos[House(\"green\")] == Pos[House(\"ivory\")] + 1\n6) Smoke(\"Old Gold\") ⟹ Pet(\"snails\")\n7) Smoke(\"Kools\") ⟹ House(\"yellow\")\n8) Pos[Drink(\"milk\")] == 3\n9) Pos[Nationality(\"Norwegian\")] == 1\n10) abs(Pos[Smoke(\"Chesterfields\")] - Pos[Pet(\"fox\")]) == 1\n11) abs(Pos[Smoke(\"Kools\")] - Pos[Pet(\"horse\")]) == 1\n12) Smoke(\"Lucky Strike\") ⟹ Drink(\"orange juice\")\n13) Nationality(\"Japanese\") ⟹ Smoke(\"Parliaments\")\n14) abs(Pos[Nationality(\"Norwegian\")] - Pos[House(\"blue\")]) == 1\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.UNSOLVED_EINSTEINS_ZEBRA","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.UNSOLVED_EINSTEINS_ZEBRA","text":"UNSOLVED_EINSTEINS_ZEBRA isa UnsolvedZebraPuzzle\n\nThis is the famous zebra puzzle that gave zebra puzzles their name. It is said to be created by Albert Einstein. You can learn more about it at the Wikipedia Zebra Puzzle entry.\n\nThe difference between this constant and EINSTEINS_ZEBRA is that this instance is not solved (does not contain the solution table).\n\nSee also EINSTEINS_ZEBRA\n\njulia> ZP.UNSOLVED_EINSTEINS_ZEBRA\nUnsolvedZebraPuzzle{5, 5, Tuple{Drink, House, Nationality, Pet, Smoke}} with 14 clues\n┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│    Drink              coffee, milk, orange juice, tea, water           │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│    House                  blue, green, ivory, red, yellow              │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ Nationality    Englishman, Japanese, Spaniard, Ukrainian, Norwegian    │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│     Pet                   dog, horse, snails, zebra, fox               │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│    Smoke     Chesterfields, Lucky Strike, Old Gold, Parliaments, Kools │\n└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\nclues:\n1) Nationality(\"Englishman\") ⟹ House(\"red\")\n2) Nationality(\"Spaniard\") ⟹ Pet(\"dog\")\n3) Drink(\"coffee\") ⟹ House(\"green\")\n4) Nationality(\"Ukrainian\") ⟹ Drink(\"tea\")\n5) Pos[House(\"green\")] == Pos[House(\"ivory\")] + 1\n6) Smoke(\"Old Gold\") ⟹ Pet(\"snails\")\n7) Smoke(\"Kools\") ⟹ House(\"yellow\")\n8) Pos[Drink(\"milk\")] == 3\n9) Pos[Nationality(\"Norwegian\")] == 1\n10) abs(Pos[Smoke(\"Chesterfields\")] - Pos[Pet(\"fox\")]) == 1\n11) abs(Pos[Smoke(\"Kools\")] - Pos[Pet(\"horse\")]) == 1\n12) Smoke(\"Lucky Strike\") ⟹ Drink(\"orange juice\")\n13) Nationality(\"Japanese\") ⟹ Smoke(\"Parliaments\")\n14) abs(Pos[Nationality(\"Norwegian\")] - Pos[House(\"blue\")]) == 1\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.AbsoluteDistance","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.AbsoluteDistance","text":"AbsoluteDistance{A,B} <: RelativePosition{A,B}\n\nA clue that states \"a::A is d places from b::B\"\n\njulia> AbsoluteDistance(House(\"red\"), Drink(\"coffee\"), 2) |> string |> print\nabs(Pos[House(\"red\")] - Pos[Drink(\"coffee\")]) == 2\njulia> ZP.check(ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA, AbsoluteDistance(House(\"red\"), Drink(\"coffee\"), 2); implied=false, duplicates=false, minimal=false)\ntrue\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.AbsolutePosition","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.AbsolutePosition","text":"AbsolutePosition{A,P} <: PositionClue\n\nA clue that states the absolute position p::P of a subject with the attribute a::A.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.Attribute","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.Attribute","text":"Attribute\n\nRepresents a possible attribute of a subject of type S.\n\nThe type parameters determine the phrase that is used for the clues and the subject strings used in the puzzle. S is the type of the subject that the Attribute can describe (Person, House, etc.)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.AttributeError","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.AttributeError","text":"AttributeError <: Exception\n\nThrown when an attribute is passed in the context of a puzzle, where this attribute is not valid.\n\nSubtypes defined in ZebraPuzzles are AttributeTypeError and AttributeVariantError\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.AttributeExprs","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.AttributeExprs","text":"AttributeExprs{K,N,P}\n\nThe IntExprs about the Attributes of a ZebraPuzzle that are used to solve the puzzle.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.AttributeQuestion","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.AttributeQuestion","text":"AttributeQuestion{A,S} <: Question\n\nA question about a specific attribute of type A of the subject type S, or position if S<:Int.\n\nThe question that an AttributeQuestion asks can be loosely stated as \"What is the attribute with type A linked to the subject s::S?\" An answer is the attribute a::A which is linked to the subject s::S.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.AttributeTypeError","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.AttributeTypeError","text":"AttributeTypeError <: AttributeError\n\nAn error thrown when an attribute has an invalid type for the given puzzle\n\nSee also check_attrtype and AttributeVariantError\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.AttributeVariantError","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.AttributeVariantError","text":"AttributeVariantError <: AttributeError\n\nAn error thrown when an attribute has a variant but the puzzle does not contain the variant of the attribute passed in the context of the puzzle.\n\nSee also check_attrvariant\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.Clue","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.Clue","text":"Clue\n\nSupertype of any clue (DirectClue, PositionClue, etc.) for a ZebraPuzzle.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.ClueError","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.ClueError","text":"ClueError <: Exception\n\nThrown when a clue is in conflict with puzzle rules or not compatible with current rules of a puzzle passed within the same context.\n\nSubtypes defined in ZebraPuzzles are DuplicateClue and ImpliedClue\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.ConflictingClue","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.ConflictingClue","text":"ConflictingClue <: ClueError\n\nThrown when trying to add a clue that is in conflict with the clues that are already in the puzzle.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.DirectClue","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.DirectClue","text":"DirectClue <: Clue\n\nA direct relationship of two attributes. I.e. PositiveClue if they belong together or NegativeClue if they dont.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.DirectionClue","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.DirectionClue","text":"DirectionClue{A,B,D} <: RelativePosition{A,B}\n\nA clue that states \"a::A is d::D of b::B\".\n\njulia> DirectionClue(House(\"red\"), Drink(\"coffee\"), ZP.d_left) |> string |> print\nPos[House(\"red\")] < Pos[Drink(\"coffee\")]\njulia> ZP.check(ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA, DirectionClue(House(\"red\"), Drink(\"coffee\"), ZP.d_left); implied=false, duplicates=false, minimal=false)\ntrue\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.Drink","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.Drink","text":"Drink <: Attribute\n\nPreferred drink of the subject.\n\nSee also EINSTEINS_ZEBRA\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.Drive","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.Drive","text":"Drive <: Attribute\n\nWhat does the subject drive.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.DuplicateClue","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.DuplicateClue","text":"DuplicateClue <: ClueError\n\nAn error thrown when trying to add a clue that is already included in the puzzle.\n\nSee also check_duplicate\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.ExactRelativePosition","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.ExactRelativePosition","text":"ExactRelativePosition{A,B,D} <: RelativePosition{A,B}\n\nA clue that states \"a::A is r::Int places in the direction of d::D from b::B\".\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.Hat","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.Hat","text":"Hat <: Attribute\n\nHat that the subject wears.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.House","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.House","text":"House <: Attribute\n\nThe house description that the subject lives in.\n\nIn most puzzles given by colour.\n\nSee also EINSTEINS_ZEBRA\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.ImpliedClue","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.ImpliedClue","text":"ImpliedClue <: ClueError\n\nAn error thrown when trying to add a clue that is implied by the rules and clues already included in the puzzle.\n\nSee also check_implied, MinimalityViolation\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.InvalidClue","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.InvalidClue","text":"InvalidClue <: ClueError\n\nThrown when a rule is in conflict with the puzzle solution table of the SolvedZebraPuzzle\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.MinimalityViolation","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.MinimalityViolation","text":"MinimalityViolation <: PuzzleError\n\nAn error thrown when the puzzle minimality would be violated by an operation.\n\nMinimality of the puzzle means that there are no clues which could be discarded and still leave the puzzle solution intact and tractable.\n\nSee also check_minimal, ImpliedClue\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.Nationality","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.Nationality","text":"Nationality <: Attribute\n\nNationality of the subject.\n\nSee also EINSTEINS_ZEBRA\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.NegativeClue","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.NegativeClue","text":"const NegativeClue = DirectClue{ct_negative::ClueType}\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.Person","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.Person","text":"Person <: Attribute\n\nThe name of the subject.\n\nSee also EINSTEINS_ZEBRA\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.Pet","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.Pet","text":"Pet <: Attribute\n\nWhich pet does the subject own.\n\nSee also EINSTEINS_ZEBRA\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.PositionClue","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.PositionClue","text":"PositionClue <: Clue\n\nA clue about the position of a subject with a specific attribute or the relation of the positions of a pair of subjects. \n\nDirect subtypes are AbsolutePosition, RelativePosition\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.PositionQuestion","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.PositionQuestion","text":"PositionQuestion{A}\n\nA question about the position of the subject with the attribute a::A.\n\nThe question that a PositionQuestion asks can be loosely stated as \"What is the position of the subject with the attribute a::A?\" An answer is the position of the subject with the attribute a::A.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.PositiveClue","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.PositiveClue","text":"const PositiveClue = DirectClue{ct_possitive::ClueType}\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.PuzzleError","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.PuzzleError","text":"PuzzleError <: Exception\n\nThrown when a puzzle would violate some optimality conditions by undergoing an operation.\n\nSubtypes defined in ZebraPuzzles are MinimalityViolation\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.Question","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.Question","text":"Question\n\nA question that can be asked about the solution of a ZebraPuzzle\n\nSubtypes are AttributeQuestion, PositionQuestion\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.RelativePosition","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.RelativePosition","text":"RelativePosition{A,B} <: PositionClue\n\nA clue about the relationship of the positions of two subjects with the attributes a::A and b::B.\n\nDirect subtypes are ExactRelativePosition, DirectionClue\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.Smoke","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.Smoke","text":"Smoke <: Attribute\n\nBrand of cigarettes that the subject smokes.\n\nSee also EINSTEINS_ZEBRA\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.SolvedZebraPuzzle","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.SolvedZebraPuzzle","text":"SolvedZebraPuzzle{K,N,Attrs} <: ZebraPuzzle{K,N,Attrs}\n\nA ZebraPuzzle that is created with a known solution table.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.UnsolvablePuzzle","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.UnsolvablePuzzle","text":"UnsolvablePuzzle <: PuzzleError\n\nThrown when calling riddle on a puzzle that is not solvable.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.UnsolvedPuzzle","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.UnsolvedPuzzle","text":"UnsolvedPuzzle <: PuzzleError\n\nThrown when show_solution or truthtable is called on an unsolved puzzle.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.UnsolvedZebraPuzzle","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.UnsolvedZebraPuzzle","text":"UnsolvedZebraPuzzle{K,N,Attrs} <: ZebraPuzzle{K,N,Attrs}\n\nA ZebraPuzzle that is created without a solution table. It has a known set of attributes and possibly a list of clues.\n\nSee also fill_clues!, solve!\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.ZebraPuzzle","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.ZebraPuzzle","text":"ZebraPuzzle{K,N,Attrs}\n\nRepresents a Zebra Puzzle, a type of logic puzzle where one deduces relationships between different subjects and their attributes based on a set of clues.\n\nType Parameters\n\nK: number of puzzle subjects and therefore also the number of distinct values of every attribute type\nN: number of attributes of per subject\nAttrs: attribute types Tuple{Attr1,Attr2,...} where Attri can be e.g. Hat, Nationality, Person or House. It has length N.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.ZebraPuzzle-Tuple{Pair{<:Type, <:Tuple{ZebraPuzzles.Attribute, Vararg{ZebraPuzzles.Attribute}}}, Vararg{Pair{<:Type, <:Tuple{ZebraPuzzles.Attribute, Vararg{ZebraPuzzles.Attribute}}}}}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.ZebraPuzzle","text":"ZebraPuzzle(attribute_variants...; clues=Clue[], questions=Question[])::UnsolvedZebraPuzzle\n\nConstruct an unsolved zebra puzzle. The puzzle holds the variants of the attributes and a solution table with missing values. Clues can be later added by add_clues!.\n\njulia> ZebraPuzzle(\n               House => (\"red\", \"blue\", \"green\"), \n               Person => (\"Martin\", \"David\", \"Lucas\"), \n               Pet => (\"Weasel\", \"Cow\", \"Mammoth\")\n           )\nUnsolvedZebraPuzzle{3, 3, Tuple{House, Person, Pet}} with no clues\n┌──────────────────────────────┐\n│ House     red, blue, green   │\n├──────────────────────────────┤\n│ Person  Martin, David, Lucas │\n├──────────────────────────────┤\n│  Pet    Weasel, Cow, Mammoth │\n└──────────────────────────────┘\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.ZebraPuzzle-Union{Tuple{Attrs}, Tuple{Attrs, Vararg{Attrs}}} where Attrs<:Tuple{ZebraPuzzles.Attribute, Vararg{ZebraPuzzles.Attribute}}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.ZebraPuzzle","text":"ZebraPuzzle(linked_attributes...; clues=Clue[], questions=Question[])::SolvedZebraPuzzle\n\nConstruct a solved zebra puzzle with the solution table zpairs with no clues. Clues can be later added by add_clues!.\n\njulia> ZebraPuzzle(\n           (Person(\"Martin\"), Hat(\"fedora\"), Nationality(\"czech\")),\n           (Person(\"David\"), Hat(\"beanie\"), Nationality(\"spanish\")),\n           (Person(\"Lucas\"), Hat(\"cap\"), Nationality(\"german\")),\n           (Person(\"Lucy\"), Hat(\"baret\"), Nationality(\"american\"))\n       )\nSolvedZebraPuzzle{4, 3, Tuple{Person, Hat, Nationality}} with no clues\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Nationality   Hat    Person │\n├─────────────────────────────┤\n│    czech     fedora  Martin │\n├─────────────────────────────┤\n│   spanish    beanie  David  │\n├─────────────────────────────┤\n│   german      cap    Lucas  │\n├─────────────────────────────┤\n│  american    baret    Lucy  │\n└─────────────────────────────┘\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#Base.rand-Union{Tuple{Type{UnsolvedZebraPuzzle{K, N}}}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{K}} where {K, N}","page":"API Reference","title":"Base.rand","text":"Random.rand(UnsolvedZebraPuzzle{K,N}; clues=true)\n\nGenerate a random unsolved zebra puzzle with K subjects each of which has N attributes.\n\nIf clues is true, the puzzle is filled with a minimal set of random clues ensuring that it is solvable. If question is true, the puzzle is accompanied with a random question about the puzzle.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#DataAPI.ncol-Union{Tuple{ZebraPuzzle{<:Any, N}}, Tuple{N}} where N","page":"API Reference","title":"DataAPI.ncol","text":"ncol(z::ZebraPuzzle)\n\nReturns the number of columns of the solution table for the puzzle z which is equal to the number of attributes linked to each of the puzzle subjects.\n\nSee also nrow, nattr\n\njulia> ZP.ncol(ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA)\n5\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#DataAPI.nrow-Union{Tuple{ZebraPuzzle{K}}, Tuple{K}} where K","page":"API Reference","title":"DataAPI.nrow","text":"nrow(z::ZebraPuzzle)\n\nReturns the number of rows of the solution table for the puzzle z which is equal to the number of subjects the puzzle is about.\n\nSee also ncol, nattr\n\njulia> ZP.nrow(ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA)\n5\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.add_clue!-Tuple{ZebraPuzzle, Clue}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.add_clue!","text":"add_clue!(z::ZebraPuzzle, c::Clue; ischecked=false, kwargs...)\n\nAdds a single clue c to the ZebraPuzzle z.\n\nThe clue is checked (See check) prior to its addition if ischecked == false. Any other keyword arguments are passed to check.\n\nSee also add_clues!\n\njulia> z = ZP.SIMPLE_ZEBRA |> deepcopy;\n\njulia> add_clue!(z, Clue(House(\"green\"), Smoke(\"Parliaments\")))\nSolvedZebraPuzzle{3, 4, Tuple{House, Nationality, Smoke, Drink}} with 1 clues\n┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ House  Nationality     Smoke         Drink     │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  red   Englishman     Old Gold        tea      │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ green   Japanese    Parliaments      coffee    │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ ivory   Spaniard    Lucky Strike  orange juice │\n└────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\nclues:\n1) House(\"green\") ⟹ Smoke(\"Parliaments\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.add_clue!-Tuple{ZebraPuzzle}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.add_clue!","text":"add_clue!(z::ZebraPuzzle)\n\nAdds a randomly generated clue to the ZebraPuzzle z.\n\njulia> z = ZP.SIMPLE_ZEBRA |> deepcopy;\n\njulia> add_clue!(z)\nSolvedZebraPuzzle{3, 4, Tuple{House, Nationality, Smoke, Drink}} with 1 clues\n┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ House  Nationality     Smoke         Drink     │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  red   Englishman     Old Gold        tea      │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ green   Japanese    Parliaments      coffee    │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ ivory   Spaniard    Lucky Strike  orange juice │\n└────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\nclues:\n1) Pos[Nationality(\"Japanese\")] < Pos[Smoke(\"Lucky Strike\")]\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.add_clues!-Tuple{ZebraPuzzle, Vector{<:Clue}}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.add_clues!","text":"add_clues!(z::ZebraPuzzle, cs::Vector{<:Clue}; ischecked=false, kwargs...)\n\nAdds clues from cs to the ZebraPuzzle z.\n\nThe clues are checked (See check) prior to their addition if ischecked == false. Any other keyword arguments     are passed to check.\n\njulia> z = ZP.SIMPLE_ZEBRA |> deepcopy;\n\njulia> add_clues!(z, [\n            Clue(House(\"red\"), Smoke(\"Old Gold\")),\n            Clue(Nationality(\"Spaniard\"), Drink(\"orange juice\"))\n        ])\nSolvedZebraPuzzle{3, 4, Tuple{House, Nationality, Smoke, Drink}} with 2 clues\n┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ House  Nationality     Smoke         Drink     │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  red   Englishman     Old Gold        tea      │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ green   Japanese    Parliaments      coffee    │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ ivory   Spaniard    Lucky Strike  orange juice │\n└────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\nclues:\n1) House(\"red\") ⟹ Smoke(\"Old Gold\")\n2) Nationality(\"Spaniard\") ⟹ Drink(\"orange juice\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.add_question!-Tuple{ZebraPuzzle, Question}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.add_question!","text":"add_question!(z::ZebraPuzzle, q::Question; ischecked=false)\n\nAdd a question q to the ZebraPuzzle z.\n\nThe question is checked (See check) prior to its addition if ischecked == false. Any other keyword arguments are passed to check.\n\njulia> z = ZP.SIMPLE_ZEBRA |> deepcopy;\n\njulia> add_question!(z, AttributeQuestion{Drink}(House(\"red\")))\nSolvedZebraPuzzle{3, 4, Tuple{House, Nationality, Smoke, Drink}} with no clues and 1 questions\n┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ House  Nationality     Smoke         Drink     │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  red   Englishman     Old Gold        tea      │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ green   Japanese    Parliaments      coffee    │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ ivory   Spaniard    Lucky Strike  orange juice │\n└────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\nquestions:\n1) Drink[House(\"red\")]?\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.answer-Tuple{Question, ZebraPuzzle}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.answer","text":"answer(q::Question, z::ZebraPuzzle)\n\nGive the answer to the question q in the ZebraPuzzle z.\n\njulia> aq = AttributeQuestion{Smoke}(Nationality(\"Englishman\"));\n\njulia> ZP.answer(aq, ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA)\nSmoke(\"Old Gold\")\n\njulia> pq = PositionQuestion(Drink(\"water\"));\n\njulia> ZP.answer(pq, ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA)\n1\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.answer-Tuple{ZebraPuzzle}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.answer","text":"answer(puzzle::ZebraPuzzle)\n\nGive the phrases for the answers to the puzzle questions.\n\njulia> puz = ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA |> deepcopy;\n\njulia> add_question!(puz); puz.questions[1]\nPositionQuestion{House}(House(\"ivory\"))\n\njulia> ZP.answer(puz)\n\"The ivory house is in the fourth position.\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.attr_types-Tuple{Question}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.attr_types","text":"attr_types(q::Question) => Vector\n\nGet the attribute types that the question q is about\n\nEvery subtype of Question must implement this interface.\n\njulia> aq = AttributeQuestion{Smoke}(Nationality(\"Englishman\"));\n \njulia> ZP.attr_types(aq)\n2-element Vector{DataType}:\n Smoke\n Nationality\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.attributes-Tuple{Clue}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.attributes","text":"attributes(c::Clue)\n\nRetrieve the attributes that are involved in a clue.\n\nThis is mainly for checking for the correctness of the clue.\n\njulia> ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA.clues[1] |> string |> print\nNationality(\"Englishman\") ⟹ House(\"red\")\n\njulia> attributes(ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA.clues[1])\n(Nationality(\"Englishman\"), House(\"red\"))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.attributes-Tuple{Question}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.attributes","text":"attributes(q::Question) => Vector{Attribute}\n\nGet the attributes that the question q is about\n\nEvery subtype of Question must implement this interface.\n\njulia> aq = AttributeQuestion{Smoke}(Nationality(\"Englishman\"));\n\njulia> ZP.attributes(aq)\n1-element Vector{Nationality}:\n Nationality(\"Englishman\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.attributes-Tuple{SolvedZebraPuzzle, ZebraPuzzles.Attribute}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.attributes","text":"attributes(puzzle, s::Attribute)\nattributes(puzzle, s::Not{Attribute})\n\nGet the other attributes of the puzzle that are linked to the attribute s\n\njulia> attributes(ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA, Smoke(\"Old Gold\"))\n4-element Vector{ZebraPuzzles.Attribute}:\n House(\"red\")\n Nationality(\"Englishman\")\n Drink(\"milk\")\n Pet(\"snails\")\n\njulia> attributes(ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA, Not(House(\"red\")))\n20-element Vector{ZebraPuzzles.Attribute}:\n House(\"yellow\")\n House(\"blue\")\n House(\"ivory\")\n House(\"green\")\n Nationality(\"Norwegian\")\n Nationality(\"Ukrainian\")\n Nationality(\"Spaniard\")\n Nationality(\"Japanese\")\n Smoke(\"Kools\")\n Smoke(\"Chesterfields\")\n Smoke(\"Lucky Strike\")\n Smoke(\"Parliaments\")\n Drink(\"water\")\n Drink(\"tea\")\n Drink(\"orange juice\")\n Drink(\"coffee\")\n Pet(\"fox\")\n Pet(\"horse\")\n Pet(\"dog\")\n Pet(\"zebra\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.attributes-Tuple{ZebraPuzzle, InvertedIndex{<:Type}}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.attributes","text":"attributes(puzzle::ZebraPuzzle, S::Not{<:Type{<:Attribute}})\n\nGet the attributes of the puzzle other than the given type S.\n\nEvery subtype of ZebraPuzzle must implement this interface.\n\njulia> attributes(ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA, Not(Smoke))\n20-element Vector{ZebraPuzzles.Attribute}:\n House(\"yellow\")\n House(\"blue\")\n House(\"red\")\n House(\"ivory\")\n House(\"green\")\n Nationality(\"Norwegian\")\n Nationality(\"Ukrainian\")\n Nationality(\"Englishman\")\n Nationality(\"Spaniard\")\n Nationality(\"Japanese\")\n Drink(\"water\")\n Drink(\"tea\")\n Drink(\"milk\")\n Drink(\"orange juice\")\n Drink(\"coffee\")\n Pet(\"fox\")\n Pet(\"horse\")\n Pet(\"snails\")\n Pet(\"dog\")\n Pet(\"zebra\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.attributes-Tuple{ZebraPuzzle, Type{<:ZebraPuzzles.Attribute}}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.attributes","text":"attributes(puzzle::ZebraPuzzle, S::Type{<:Attribute})\n\nGet the attributes of the puzzle of the given type s.\n\nEvery subtype of ZebraPuzzle must implement this interface.\n\njulia> attributes(ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA, Smoke)\n5-element Vector{Smoke}:\n Smoke(\"Kools\")\n Smoke(\"Chesterfields\")\n Smoke(\"Old Gold\")\n Smoke(\"Lucky Strike\")\n Smoke(\"Parliaments\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.attributes-Tuple{ZebraPuzzle}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.attributes","text":"attributes(puzzle::ZebraPuzzle)\n\nGet all the attributes of the puzzle\n\nEvery subtype of ZebraPuzzle must implement this interface.\n\njulia> attributes(ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA)\n25-element Vector{ZebraPuzzles.Attribute}:\n House(\"yellow\")\n House(\"blue\")\n House(\"red\")\n House(\"ivory\")\n House(\"green\")\n Nationality(\"Norwegian\")\n Nationality(\"Ukrainian\")\n Nationality(\"Englishman\")\n Nationality(\"Spaniard\")\n Nationality(\"Japanese\")\n ⋮\n Drink(\"tea\")\n Drink(\"milk\")\n Drink(\"orange juice\")\n Drink(\"coffee\")\n Pet(\"fox\")\n Pet(\"horse\")\n Pet(\"snails\")\n Pet(\"dog\")\n Pet(\"zebra\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.attrtypes-Union{Tuple{ZebraPuzzle{<:Any, <:Any, Attrs}}, Tuple{Attrs}} where Attrs","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.attrtypes","text":"attrtypes(puzzle)\n\nGet the attribute parameters of the puzzle\n\njulia> ZP.attrtypes(ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA)\n5-element Vector{DataType}:\n House\n Nationality\n Drink\n Smoke\n Pet\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.check-Tuple{SolvedZebraPuzzle, Clue}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.check","text":"check(puzzle::SolvedZebraPuzzle, c::Clue; <kwargs>)\n\nImplementation of the check interface for ZebraPuzzle that includes a clue validity check against the solution table.\n\nSee also check_valid\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\nKeyword arguments control which of the checks are controlled for the clue.\n\nduplicates=true – clue is not already included in the puzzle?\nvalid=true –  clue is valid under the solution table?\ntypes=true –  clue has valid attribute types for the puzzle?\nvariants=true – clue has valid attribute variants (\"names\") for the puzzle?\nimplied=true – clue is not implied by the clues in the puzzle?\nminimal=true – clue is needed for the solution? I.e. current clues do not suffice for getting the full solution.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.check-Tuple{UnsolvedZebraPuzzle, Clue}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.check","text":"check(puzzle::SolvedZebraPuzzle, c::Clue; <kwargs>)\n\nImplementation of the check interface for ZebraPuzzle that includes a clue validity check against the solution table.\n\nSee also check_valid\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\nKeyword arguments control which of the checks are controlled for the clue.\n\nduplicates=true – clue is not already included in the puzzle?\nvalid=true –  clue is not in contradiction with the puzzle clues?\ntypes=true –  clue has valid attribute types for the puzzle?\nvariants=true – clue has valid attribute variants (\"names\") for the puzzle?\nimplied=true – clue is not implied by the clues in the puzzle?\nminimal=true – clue is needed for the solution? I.e. current clues do not suffice for getting the full solution.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.check-Tuple{ZebraPuzzle, Clue}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.check","text":"check(z::ZebraPuzzle, c::Clue)\n\nCheck that the clue c is compatible with the puzzle z. \n\nAll subtypes of ZebraPuzzle must implement this interface\n\nSee also check_attrtype, check_attrvariant, check_minimal, check_implied\n\njulia> all(ZP.check.(fill(ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA), ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA.clues; duplicates=false, minimal=false, implied=false))\ntrue\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.check-Tuple{ZebraPuzzle, Question}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.check","text":"check(z::ZebraPuzzle, q::Question, types=true, variants=true)\n\nImplementation of the check interface for ZebraPuzzle that checks the questions q for valid types and attribute variants.\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\nKeyword arguments control which of the checks are controlled for the clue.\n\ntypes=true –  question has valid attribute types for the puzzle?\nvariants=true – question has valid attribute variants (\"names\") for the puzzle?\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.check_attrtype-Tuple{ZebraPuzzle, Type{<:ZebraPuzzles.Attribute}}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.check_attrtype","text":"check_attrtype(puzzle, s::Type{<:Attribute})\ncheck_attrtype(puzzle, s::Attribute)\n\nCheck that the attribute of type s is a valid attribute type in the puzzle\n\njulia> ZP.check_attrtype(ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA, House)\ntrue\n\njulia> ZP.check_attrtype(ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA, House(\"red\"))\ntrue\n\njulia> ZP.check_attrtype(ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA, House(\"pink\")) # !!! This only checks the type !!!\ntrue\n\njulia> ZP.check_attrtype(ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA, Hat)\nERROR: AttributeTypeError: attribute type `Hat` is invalid for the given puzzle. Valid types are `DataType[House, Nationality, Drink, Smoke, Pet]`\n[...]\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.check_attrvariant-Tuple{ZebraPuzzle, ZebraPuzzles.Attribute}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.check_attrvariant","text":"check_attrvariant(puzzle, s::Attribute)\n\nCheck that the attribute variant s is included in the puzzle.\n\nwarning: Warning\nAssumes that the attribute type typeof(s) is valid for the puzzle.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.check_duplicate-Tuple{ZebraPuzzle, Clue}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.check_duplicate","text":"check_duplicate(puzzle, c::Clue)\n\nCheck that the clue c is not already included in the puzzle.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.check_implied","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.check_implied","text":"check_implied(puzzle, c::Clue, exprs::AttributeExprs=AttributeExprs(puzzle))\n\nCheck that the clue c is not implied by the rules and clues already included in the puzzle.\n\njulia> z = ZebraPuzzle(Drink => (\"coffee\", \"tea\"), Smoke => (\"Old Gold\", \"Chesterfields\"), House => (\"green\", \"red\"));\n\njulia> ZP.add_clue!(z, Clue(House(\"red\"), Smoke(\"Old Gold\")));\n\njulia> ZP.add_clue!(z, Clue(Smoke(\"Old Gold\"), Drink(\"tea\")))\nUnsolvedZebraPuzzle{2, 3, Tuple{Drink, Smoke, House}} with 2 clues\n┌────────────────────────────────┐\n│ Drink        coffee, tea       │\n├────────────────────────────────┤\n│ Smoke  Old Gold, Chesterfields │\n├────────────────────────────────┤\n│ House        green, red        │\n└────────────────────────────────┘\n\nclues:\n1) House(\"red\") ⟹ Smoke(\"Old Gold\")\n2) Smoke(\"Old Gold\") ⟹ Drink(\"tea\")\n\njulia> ZP.check_implied(z, AbsolutePosition(House(\"red\"), 1)) # independent clue\ntrue\n\njulia> ZP.check_implied(z, Clue(Drink(\"tea\"), House(\"red\"))) # (red => old gold) ∧ (old gold => tea) => (red => tea)\nERROR: ImpliedClue: clue Drink(\"tea\") ⟹ House(\"red\") is implied by the rules and clues already included in the puzzle.\n[...]\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.check_minimal","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.check_minimal","text":"check_minimal(puzzle, c::Clue, exprs::AttributeExprs=AttributeExprs(puzzle))\n\nCheck that the clue c is not breaking the minimality of the puzzle clue set. I.e. that adding the additional clue is not necessary for finding the solution.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.check_valid","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.check_valid","text":"check_valid(z::UnsolvedZebraPuzzle, c::Clue, exprs=AttributeExprs(z))\n\nValidate the truth of the clue under the assertion of puzzle rules and the current puzzle clues.\n\njulia> puzzle = ZP.UNSOLVED_EINSTEINS_ZEBRA |> deepcopy;\n\njulia> empty!(puzzle.clues)\nClue[]\n\njulia> add_clue!(puzzle, Clue(House(\"blue\"), Pet(\"horse\")))\nUnsolvedZebraPuzzle{5, 5, Tuple{Drink, House, Nationality, Pet, Smoke}} with 1 clues\n┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│    Drink              coffee, milk, orange juice, tea, water           │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│    House                  blue, green, ivory, red, yellow              │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ Nationality    Englishman, Japanese, Spaniard, Ukrainian, Norwegian    │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│     Pet                   dog, horse, snails, zebra, fox               │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│    Smoke     Chesterfields, Lucky Strike, Old Gold, Parliaments, Kools │\n└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\nclues:\n1) House(\"blue\") ⟹ Pet(\"horse\")\n\njulia> ZP.check_valid(puzzle, Clue(House(\"red\"), Pet(\"horse\")))\nERROR: ConflictingClue: clue House(\"red\") ⟹ Pet(\"horse\") is in conflict with the current rules/clues in the puzzle.\n[...]\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.check_valid-Tuple{SolvedZebraPuzzle, ZebraPuzzles.DirectClue}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.check_valid","text":"check_valid(z::SolvedZebraPuzzle, c::Clue)\n\nValidate the truth of the clue against the solution table of the puzzle.\n\nwarning: Warning\nIt does not checked against the clues included in the puzzle.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.col-Tuple{Type{<:ZebraPuzzles.Attribute}}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.col","text":"col(S::Type{<:Attribute})\ncol(s::Attribute)\n\nGet the name of the column of attribute s / of the type S in the solution table.\n\njulia> ZP.col(House(\"red\"))\n:House\n\njulia> ZP.col(House)\n:House\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.fill_clues!-Tuple{ZebraPuzzle}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.fill_clues!","text":"fill_clues!(puzzle::ZebraPuzzle)\n\nAdd random clues until the puzzle has a minimal set and ensures a unique solution.\n\njulia> z = ZebraPuzzle(\n           Drink => (\"coffee\", \"tea\"),\n           Smoke => (\"Old Gold\", \"Chesterfields\"), \n           House => (\"green\", \"red\")\n       );\n\njulia> ZP.fill_clues!(z)\nUnsolvedZebraPuzzle{2, 3, Tuple{Drink, Smoke, House}} with 3 clues\n┌────────────────────────────────┐\n│ Drink        coffee, tea       │\n├────────────────────────────────┤\n│ Smoke  Old Gold, Chesterfields │\n├────────────────────────────────┤\n│ House        green, red        │\n└────────────────────────────────┘\n\nclues:\n1) Pos[Drink(\"coffee\")] > Pos[Drink(\"tea\")]\n2) Pos[House(\"green\")] == 2\n3) Drink(\"tea\") ⟹ ¬Smoke(\"Chesterfields\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.has_unique_solution","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.has_unique_solution","text":"has_unique_solution(z::ZebraPuzzle)\n\nCheck whether the clues of the puzzle lead to one unique solution.\n\njulia> ZP.has_unique_solution(ZP.UNSOLVED_EINSTEINS_ZEBRA)\ntrue\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.id-Tuple{ZebraPuzzles.Attribute}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.id","text":"id(a::Attribute)\n\nSatisfiability variable name.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.indexof-Tuple{ZebraPuzzle, Type{<:ZebraPuzzles.Attribute}}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.indexof","text":"indexof(z::ZebraPuzzle, A::Type{<:Attribute})\nindexof(z::ZebraPuzzle, a::Attribute)\n\nReturn the internal index of the attribute / attribute type\n\nThis internal index is used indexing into the AttributeExprs of the puzzle, which holds the Satisfiability.jl variable used for solving the puzzle. \n\nEvery subtype of ZebraPuzzle must implement this interface.\n\njulia> ZP.indexof(ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA, Smoke(\"Chesterfields\"))\n(2, 3)\n\njulia> ZP.indexof(ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA, Smoke)\n3\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.issolved-Tuple{UnsolvedZebraPuzzle}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.issolved","text":"issolved(puzzle::UnsolvedZebraPuzzle)\n\nCheck whether the puzzle was solved by solve! and has a solution without missing keys.\n\njulia> z = ZP.UNSOLVED_EINSTEINS_ZEBRA |> deepcopy;\n\njulia> ZP.issolved(z)\nfalse\n\njulia> solve!(z);\n\njulia> ZP.issolved(z)\ntrue\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.nattr-Tuple{ZebraPuzzle}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.nattr","text":"nattr(z::ZebraPuzzle)\n\nReturns the total number of attributes of the puzzle z which is equal to nrow(z) * ncol(z)\n\nSee also nrow, ncol\n\njulia> ZP.nattr(ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA)\n25\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.nclue-Tuple{ZebraPuzzle}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.nclue","text":"nclue(puzzle)\n\nGet the number of clues of the puzzle.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.nquestion-Tuple{ZebraPuzzle}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.nquestion","text":"nquestion(puzzle)\n\nGet the number of questions of the puzzle.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.phrase-Tuple{Question}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.phrase","text":"phrase(q::Question) => String\n\nGet a string representation of the question q\n\nEvery subtype of Question must implement this interface\n\njulia> aq = AttributeQuestion{Smoke}(Nationality(\"Englishman\"));\n\njulia> ZP.phrase(aq)\n\"What cigarette brand does the Englishman prefer?\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.riddle-Union{Tuple{ZebraPuzzle{K}}, Tuple{K}} where K","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.riddle","text":"riddle(puzzle::ZebraPuzzle; <kwargs>)\n\nReturn the string of the zebra puzzle introduction and clues in natural language.\n\nThe string uses markdown for bullet points or numbers and prints the Markdown using the context IO.\n\nIf introduction=false is (default true) the introduction such as \"There are five houses.\" is skipped. If bulletpoints=true, the clues are prefixed with \"- \" and if numbers=true the clues are prefixed with \"i)\". If both are false the clues only have a space between them.\n\nIf quiet=true the riddle is not printed but only returned as a string.\n\nSee also solve!\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.rules-Union{Tuple{ZebraPuzzles.AttributeExprs{K}}, Tuple{K}} where K","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.rules","text":"rules(exprs::AttributeExprs)::BoolExpr\nrules(puzzle::ZebraPuzzle)::Tuple{AttributeExprs, BoolExpr}\n\nGenerate the zebra puzzle Satisfiability.jl rules for the attributes return the rule assertion BoolExpr. If a ZebraPuzzle is passed, it first generates the AttributeExprs and then returns the (exprs, rules) tuple.\n\njulia> z = ZebraPuzzle(Drink => (\"coffee\", \"tea\"), House => (\"green\", \"red\"))\nUnsolvedZebraPuzzle{2, 2, Tuple{Drink, House}} with no clues\n┌────────────────────┐\n│ Drink  coffee, tea │\n├────────────────────┤\n│ House  green, red  │\n└────────────────────┘\n\n\njulia> exprs, rules = ZP.rules(z);\n\njulia> rules\n4-element Vector{Satisfiability.BoolExpr}:\n and_4a3b8ce4f0c5932b\n | leq_13a07d362557ecbd\n |  | const_1 = 1\n |  | Drink_tea\n | leq_5f49e791afe246a5\n |  | const_1 = 1\n |  | House_green\n | leq_a27b1741a1f9008e\n |  | const_1 = 1\n |  | House_red\n | leq_e94b7d8032d90182\n |  | const_1 = 1\n |  | Drink_coffee\n\n and_9b58b2ca1f5f8553\n | leq_20b3312716ae8085\n |  | House_red\n |  | const_2 = 2\n | leq_2349e5270bfc6484\n |  | Drink_tea\n |  | const_2 = 2\n | leq_4674d87e645a7ee8\n |  | Drink_coffee\n |  | const_2 = 2\n | leq_e343fa1b3fccf18b\n |  | House_green\n |  | const_2 = 2\n\n distinct_f63a38a3190ef4f4\n | Drink_coffee\n | Drink_tea\n\n distinct_7f6fa8abcc538373\n | House_green\n | House_red\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.show_solution-Tuple{UnsolvedZebraPuzzle}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.show_solution","text":"show_solution(puzzle::UnsolvedZebraPuzzle)\n\nIf the puzzle was solved by solve!, converts the puzzle to a SolvedZebraPuzzle shows it.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.solve!-Tuple{UnsolvedZebraPuzzle}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.solve!","text":"solve!(puzzle::UnsolvedZebraPuzzle)\n\nSolve the zebra puzzle and fill in the solution table.\n\nSee also show_solution\n\njulia> puz = ZP.UNSOLVED_EINSTEINS_ZEBRA |> deepcopy;\n\njulia> solve!(puz);\n\njulia> puz |> ZP.show_solution\nSolvedZebraPuzzle{5, 5, NTuple{5, Union{Missing, ZebraPuzzles.Attribute}}}\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│    Drink      House   Nationality   Pet        Smoke     │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│    water      yellow   Norwegian    fox        Kools     │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│     tea        blue    Ukrainian   horse   Chesterfields │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│     milk       red    Englishman   snails    Old Gold    │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ orange juice  ivory    Spaniard     dog    Lucky Strike  │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│    coffee     green    Japanese    zebra    Parliaments  │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.titlecase-Tuple{String}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.titlecase","text":"titlecase(s::String)\n\nUpper-case the first letter of the string\n\njulia> ZP.titlecase(\"red house\")\n\"Red house\"\n\njulia> ZP.titlecase(\"apple\")\n\"Apple\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.toclue-Tuple{Question, ZebraPuzzle}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.toclue","text":"toclue(q::Question, puz::ZebraPuzzle)\n\nGet the clue that corresponds to the question q in the puzzle.\n\nThrows an UnsolvedPuzzle error if the puzzle is not solved.\n\njulia> ZP.toclue(AttributeQuestion{Smoke}(Nationality(\"Englishman\")), ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA)\nPositiveClue{Nationality, Smoke}(Nationality(\"Englishman\"), Smoke(\"Old Gold\"))\n\njulia> ZP.toclue(PositionQuestion(Smoke(\"Parliaments\")), ZP.EINSTEINS_ZEBRA)\nAbsolutePosition{Smoke, Int64}(Smoke(\"Parliaments\"), 5, 5)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.truthtable-Tuple{ZebraPuzzle}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.truthtable","text":"truthtable(puzzle::ZebraPuzzle)\n\nGet the truth table of the puzzle.\n\nThrows a PuzzleError if the puzzle is not solved yet.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#ZebraPuzzles.variants-Tuple{Type{<:ZebraPuzzles.Attribute}}","page":"API Reference","title":"ZebraPuzzles.variants","text":"variants(A::Type{<:Attribute})\n\nReturns known variants of the attribute type A.\n\nThese are used for generating random puzzles.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ZebraPuzzles.jl","page":"Home","title":"ZebraPuzzles.jl 🦓","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Welcome to the documentation for ZebraPuzzles.jl!","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"ZebraPuzzles is a Julia package for the logical puzzles of the zebra type. It provides a framework for defining puzzles, adding clues about the puzzle, and finding a solution which satisfies the clues.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Getting-Started","page":"Home","title":"Getting Started 🚀","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"To get started, you'll need to define a puzzle. A puzzle is defined by a set of attributes and a set of clues.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Defining-a-Puzzle","page":"Home","title":"Defining a Puzzle 🗺️","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"A zebra puzzle is characterized by a number of subjects and a number of attribute types of which every subject has a unique variant.","category":"page"},{"location":"#ZebraPuzzles.ZebraPuzzle-index","page":"Home","title":"ZebraPuzzles.ZebraPuzzle","text":"ZebraPuzzle{K,N,Attrs}\n\nRepresents a Zebra Puzzle, a type of logic puzzle where one deduces relationships between different subjects and their attributes based on a set of clues.\n\nType Parameters\n\nK: number of puzzle subjects and therefore also the number of distinct values of every attribute type\nN: number of attributes of per subject\nAttrs: attribute types Tuple{Attr1,Attr2,...} where Attri can be e.g. Hat, Nationality, Person or House. It has length N.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"There are two forms of a puzzle that you may want to create.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"If you would like to have a puzzle that is not yet solved (for example with the intention of solving it later), you can define it by stating the variants of attributes that can be associated with a subject.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Unsolved Puzzle: A puzzle which has a set of variants for each attribute type, but they are not yet grouped as belonging to a single subject. (UnsolvedZebraPuzzle)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using ZebraPuzzles # hide\nusing ZebraPuzzles: ZebraPuzzles as ZP # hide\npuz_unsolved = ZebraPuzzle(\n    Drink => (\"coffee\", \"milk\", \"orange juice\", \"tea\", \"water\"),\n    House => (\"blue\", \"green\", \"ivory\", \"red\", \"yellow\"),\n    Nationality => (\"Englishman\", \"Japanese\", \"Spaniard\", \"Ukrainian\", \"Norwegian\"),\n    Pet => (\"dog\", \"horse\", \"snails\", \"zebra\", \"fox\"),\n    Smoke => (\"Chesterfields\", \"Lucky Strike\", \"Old Gold\", \"Parliaments\", \"Kools\"),\n)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Solved Puzzle: A puzzle which is defined by a truth table, which specifies which attributes belong together. (SolvedZebraPuzzle)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using ZebraPuzzles # hide\npuz_solved = ZebraPuzzle(\n    (House(\"yellow\"), Nationality(\"Norwegian\"), Drink(\"water\"), Smoke(\"Kools\"), Pet(\"fox\")),\n    (House(\"blue\"), Nationality(\"Ukrainian\"), Drink(\"tea\"), Smoke(\"Chesterfields\"), Pet(\"horse\")),\n    (House(\"red\"), Nationality(\"Englishman\"), Drink(\"milk\"), Smoke(\"Old Gold\"), Pet(\"snails\")),\n    (House(\"ivory\"), Nationality(\"Spaniard\"), Drink(\"orange juice\"), Smoke(\"Lucky Strike\"), Pet(\"dog\")),\n    (House(\"green\"), Nationality(\"Japanese\"), Drink(\"coffee\"), Smoke(\"Parliaments\"), Pet(\"zebra\")),\n)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Both of these puzzle types can contain clues which can lead the solver to a solution and in order to define a puzzle that is solvable, you need to add these to enable a solver to infer it.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Adding-Clues","page":"Home","title":"Adding Clues 📐","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"There are various types of clues that can help solve a zebra puzzle. They may hint towards the position of the subject in relation to other subjects (direction, distance, etc.) or relation of the attributes (belong together, do not belong together, etc.). Clues may be added to the puzzle by directly specifying them and adding them with add_clue!","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"add_clue!(\n    puz_unsolved,\n    Clue(Drink(\"coffee\"), Pet(\"snails\")) # attributes \"coffee\" and \"snails\" belong together\n)\nnothing # hide","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"and they are checked for consistency with the puzzle in the process so that they do not contradict the previous clues. Checking the clues may also be done separately by the check function","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"ZP.check(\n    puz_unsolved,\n    Clue(Drink(\"coffee\"), Not(Pet(\"snails\")))\n) # ❌ inconsistent clue (contradiction)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"It does not only control the consistency of the clues but also checks that the clue is not implied by the previous ones to assure the minimality property of the puzzle clue set.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"add_clue!(puz_unsolved, Clue(House(\"ivory\"), Pet(\"snails\")));\nZP.check(puz_unsolved, Clue(Drink(\"coffee\"), House(\"ivory\"))) # ❌ clue implied by the previous ones","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"You can also add multiple clues at once with add_clues!","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"add_clues!(puz_unsolved, \n    [\n         ExactRelativePosition(House(\"green\"), House(\"ivory\"), 1),\n         Clue(Smoke(\"Old Gold\"), Pet(\"snails\")),\n         Clue(Smoke(\"Kools\"), House(\"yellow\")),\n         AbsolutePosition(Drink(\"milk\"), 3),\n         AbsolutePosition(Nationality(\"Norwegian\"), 1),\n         AbsoluteDistance(Smoke(\"Chesterfields\"), Pet(\"fox\"), 1),\n         AbsoluteDistance(Smoke(\"Kools\"), Pet(\"horse\"), 1),\n         Clue(Smoke(\"Lucky Strike\"), Drink(\"orange juice\")),\n    ]\n)\nnothing # hide","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"It is also possible to fill clues so that the puzzle is solvable (uniquely) using fill_clues!","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using Random # hide\nRandom.seed!(42) # hide\nfill_clues!(puz_unsolved)\nnothing # hide","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"We end up with a uniquely solvable puzzle with a minimal number of clues (i.e. any clue removal leads to non-uniqueness/insolubility).","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"puz_unsolved","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"All of the above methods can also be used for the solved puzzle and additionally the correctness of the clues against the solution is checked","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"add_clue!(puz_solved, Clue(Drink(\"milk\"), House(\"green\")))","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Clues are filled so that they are in accordance with the puzzles truth table","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using Random # hide\nRandom.seed!(42) # hide\nfill_clues!(puz_solved)","category":"page"},{"location":"#Question","page":"Home","title":"Question ❓","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"You may not want to require the full truth table as the solution. In this case, you may want to phrase a specific Question about the puzzle. You can either ask a question about an attribute of a subject (AttributeQuestion)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Random.seed!(42) # hide\nattrq = rand(AttributeQuestion, puz_unsolved)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"or a question about the position of a subject (PositionQuestion)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Random.seed!(42) # hide\nposq = rand(PositionQuestion, puz_unsolved)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Similarly to the case of clues, we can add a question to the puzzle with add_question!.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Random-Puzzle-Generation","page":"Home","title":"Random Puzzle Generation 🎲","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Puzzles with a given number of attributes and subject can also be randomly generated","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using ZebraPuzzles # hide\nusing Random # hide\nRandom.seed!(42) # hide\nrand(UnsolvedZebraPuzzle{3,3})","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using ZebraPuzzles # hide\nusing Random # hide\nRandom.seed!(42) # hide\nrand(UnsolvedZebraPuzzle{3,4})","category":"page"},{"location":"#Solving-the-Puzzle","page":"Home","title":"Solving the Puzzle 🧠","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Even if the puzzle has the clues to ensure a unique solution, it is still unsolved.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"@assert ZP.issolved(puz_unsolved) == false","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"To solve an unsolved puzzle, you can call the solve! function.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"solve!(puz_unsolved);\nnothing # hide","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This will add the truth table to the puz_unsolved. You can check that it now contains the solution with issolved","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"@assert ZP.issolved(puz_unsolved) == true","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"and you can inspect the solution using show_solution","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"puz_unsolved |> ZebraPuzzles.show_solution","category":"page"},{"location":"#Natural-Language","page":"Home","title":"Natural Language 📖","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"If you would like to give the puzzle to someone (person 🤦 or an AI agent 🤖), you probably want to have it in natural language phrasing. You can get this using the function riddle","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Random.seed!(42) # hide\nriddle(puz_unsolved)\nnothing # hide","category":"page"}]
}
